UMCS.util
Interface Trie

All Known Implementing Classes:
CompressedTrie
public interface Trie

Abstract Datatype for efficiently storing strings of arbitrary length. For example: 

   Trie t = new CompressedTrie();
   t.insert("Computer");
   t.insert("Cooperation");
   t.insert("Apple");
   t.insert("Comsumer");
   TrieEnumerator te = t.findPrefix("co");

Author:
Jeroen Donkers
See Also:
TriePos, CompressedTrie, TrieEnumerator

Method Detail

insert

public TriePos insert(java.lang.String v,
                      java.lang.Object c)
Insert a string into the Trie, and link a content object to this string. If the string is already present, the new content is rejected. If c is null, it is replaced by the NILL content. The function returns a reference to the newly added position.

Parameters:
v - The string that is to be stored.
c - The object that is to be stored at the position of v.
Returns:
The position of the new string, if inserted, else null.
See Also:
TriePos

public TriePos insert(java.lang.String v)
